<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880107-0118 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: American Brands Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AMB WNEWS </CO><DATELINE> AMERICAN BRANDS INC.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Charles H. Mullen was named chief executive officer of American Tobacco Co., a Stamford, Conn.-based tobacco subsidiary of this financial services, distilled spirits and tobacco concern. He remains president. No successor has been named to the chief operating officer post at the unit. Mr. Mullen succeeds Thomas C. Hays, who remains chairman of American Tobacco. Mr. Hays also became president and chief operating officer of American Brands at the beginning of the year. </TEXT></DOC>